## Errors & Mistakes
- First full-file run: test_delete_current_latest_promotes_prior_surviving_version
  failed with "DB::Exception: Could not find symbol _memcmpSmallCharsAllowOverflow15
  (CANNOT_COMPILE_CODE) (version 26.5.2.39 (official build))". macOS official
  builds cannot resolve JIT symbols (Mach-O underscore prefix). Disabling
  compile_expressions + compile_aggregate_expressions did NOT fix it — the
  third JIT path, compile_sort_description (default 1, kicks in after 3 sorts,
  hence order-dependent), was the actual trigger. All three are now 0 in the
  local users.xml profile.
- `import resource` at module top would have broken Windows CI at plugin import
  time (module is imported unconditionally via pytest_plugins). Wrapped in
  try/except ImportError.
- Every run emitted PytestAssertRewriteWarning "module already imported" because
  clickhouse_server.py imports clickhouse_local before pytest registers it as a
  plugin. Fixed with PYTEST_DONT_REWRITE in the module docstring.
- zsh footguns: `echo ===X===` triggers zsh =cmd expansion; `VAR=1 time cmd`
  is a parse error (time is a keyword); rg -r is --replace, not recursive.
- Benchmark accounting trap: `time` on the pytest pipeline includes the REAPED
  local server's CPU (it's a pytest child), docker's server CPU is invisible.
  The scary "150s system time" was mostly this artifact. Compare wall only.

