## Codebase Discoveries
- ClickHouse JIT has THREE independent settings; compile_sort_description is the
  one everyone forgets.
- With an explicit --config-file, system.*_log tables are simply absent unless
  configured (verified: groupArray(name) = []). The docker image's default
  config enables them.
- users.d merging follows the users.xml location (user_directories/users_xml),
  verified empirically.
- clickhouse server forks a clickhouse-watchdog parent; process-group SIGKILL
  handles both.
- system.tables total_rows over-counts under lightweight-delete masks and patch
  parts — safe direction for dirty-table detection (never skips a dirty table).

