## Amendment (post-first-CI-round)
First CI round was fully green but exposed a JIT regression: PR2's same-job
comparison showed local-CH 319-344s vs docker-CH 276-297s on
trace_calls_complete_only and 323-340s vs 231-258s on trace — the all-platform
JIT disable was the cause (heavy xdist shards repeat aggregation/sort shapes
thousands of times). Amended so JIT is disabled ONLY on macOS (where official
builds crash with CANNOT_COMPILE_CODE); Linux keeps docker parity. Light
shards already showed local ~10% faster than docker (trace_server 154-162 vs
175-178), so post-amend the heavy shards should land at docker-minus-overhead.
